To switch from Java Swing to JavaFX in your quiz app, here's what you need to do:

## 1. **Add JavaFX Dependencies**

**If using Maven** (add to `pom.xml`):
```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.openjfx</groupId>
    <artifactId>javafx-controls</artifactId>
    <version>21.0.1</version>
</dependency>
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.openjfx</groupId>
    <artifactId>javafx-fxml</artifactId>
    <version>21.0.1</version>
</dependency>
```

**If using Gradle** (add to `build.gradle`):
```gradle
dependencies {
    implementation 'org.openjfx:javafx-controls:21.0.1'
    implementation 'org.openjfx:javafx-fxml:21.0.1'
}
```

## 2. **Key Differences: Swing → JavaFX**

| Swing | JavaFX |
|-------|--------|
| `JFrame` | `Stage` |
| `JPanel` | `Pane`, `VBox`, `HBox` |
| `JButton` | `Button` |
| `JLabel` | `Label` |
| `JTextField` | `TextField` |
| `JRadioButton` | `RadioButton` |
| `ActionListener` | `EventHandler<ActionEvent>` |

## 3. **Replace Main.java (Entry Point)**

**Old Swing way:**
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        MainFrame frame = new MainFrame();
        frame.setVisible(true);
    }
}
```

**New JavaFX way:**
```java
import javafx.application.Application;
import javafx.stage.Stage;

public class Main extends Application {
    @Override
    public void start(Stage primaryStage) throws Exception {
        MainFrame frame = new MainFrame();
        frame.show(primaryStage);  // Pass the Stage
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        launch(args);
    }
}
```

## 4. **Example: Rewrite MainFrame (Swing → JavaFX)**

**Old Swing:**
```java
public class MainFrame extends JFrame {
    public MainFrame() {
        setTitle("Quiz App");
        setSize(600, 400);
        JButton btn = new JButton("Take Quiz");
        add(btn);
    }
}
```

**New JavaFX:**
```java
import javafx.scene.Scene;
import javafx.scene.control.Button;
import javafx.scene.layout.VBox;
import javafx.stage.Stage;

public class MainFrame {
    public void show(Stage stage) {
        VBox root = new VBox(10);  // VBox with 10px spacing

        Button btn = new Button("Take Quiz");
        btn.setOnAction(e -> handleTakeQuiz());

        root.getChildren().add(btn);

        Scene scene = new Scene(root, 600, 400);
        stage.setTitle("Quiz App");
        stage.setScene(scene);
        stage.show();
    }

    private void handleTakeQuiz() {
        System.out.println("Quiz started");
    }
}
```

## 5. **Quick Comparison Chart**

| Task | Swing | JavaFX |
|------|-------|--------|
| Create window | `new JFrame()` | `new Stage()` |
| Add content | `frame.add(component)` | `scene = new Scene(root)` |
| Button click | `btn.addActionListener()` | `btn.setOnAction()` |
| Layout | `BorderLayout`, `FlowLayout` | `VBox`, `HBox`, `GridPane` |
| Styling | Look & Feel | CSS |

